grafana/grafana#113663.body:
### What happened?

If you have a join by field (tabular) transformation that is configured to join on a field that doesn't exist in any of the input data, the transformation crashes with a `cannot access property 0, P is undefined` error.

Browser stack trace points me to this line as the source of the error, suggesting that `rtable` is undefined https://github.com/grafana/grafana/blob/47f3073ab84f8654bfda65edb4112cd73d065ce4/packages/grafana-data/src/transformations/transformers/joinDataFrames.ts#L272 

### What did you expect to happen?

It doesn't crash

### Did this work before?

Unsure!

### How do we reproduce it?

See the below dashboard - change the variable to `crash` to trigger the error.

The reproduction is slightly contrived, but it can easily happen with Prometheus instant table queries that return 0 results, because they don't return columns for any of the labels.

