grafana/grafana#120212.body:
### Description

Dashboard version history is broken for large dashboards (~3MB+ per version) in Grafana Cloud. The unified storage server enforces a 2MB page limit (`MaxPageSizeBytes`) on history API responses, but the frontend `listDashboardHistory` makes a single request without auto-paginating. This causes users to see only 1-3 versions instead of the full history.

Additionally, `UnifiedDashboardAPI.listDashboardHistory` (the default API client for Cloud) has three bugs in its v1/v2 history merging logic that will become critical as v2 dashboards roll out.

**Introduced in**: https://github.com/grafana/grafana/pull/114686

### Root cause

The backend returns paginated responses when entries exceed 2MB total (`pkg/storage/unified/resource/server.go:344`). For a 3MB dashboard, only 1 entry fits per page. The response includes a `continue` token for the next page, but the frontend never follows it.

### Bugs

**1. `listDashboardHistory` doesn't paginate** (`public/app/features/dashboard/api/v1.ts:230`, `v2.ts` equivalent)
- Makes a single request, returns truncated result as-is.
- Note: `getDashboardHistoryVersions` at `v1.ts:239` already implements the correct pagination pattern (do/while loop), but it's only used for diff/restore — not for the version list.

**2. `UnifiedDashboardAPI.listDashboardHistory`** (`public/app/features/dashboard/api/UnifiedDashboardAPI.ts:65-81`)
- **Bug A**: `filteredV1Items.length === v1Response.items.length` passes trivially when both are 0, skipping v2 entirely. Pure v2 dashboards show empty history.
- **Bug B**: Neither the v1 nor v2 fetch paginates, so the merge combines two truncated pages.
- **Bug C**: When merging, `{ ...v2Response, items: merged }` preserves only the v2 continue token — v1 pagination state is lost, causing duplicates on subsequent pages.

### Proposed fix

**Part 1: Add auto-pagination to `K8sDashboardAPI` and `K8sDashboardV2API`**

Add a pagination loop to `listDashboardHistory` in both `v1.ts` and `v2.ts` that exhausts all pages before returning — same pattern as existing `getDashboardHistoryVersions`:

```typescript
async listDashboardHistory(uid: string, options?: ListDashboardHistoryOptions) {
  const limit = options?.limit ?? 10;
  const result = await this.client.list({
    labelSelector: 'grafana.app/get-history=true',
    fieldSelector: `metadata.name=${uid}`,
    limit,
    continue: options?.continueToken,
  });

  let continueToken = result.metadata.continue;
  while (result.items.length < limit && continueToken) {
    const nextPage = await this.client.list({
      labelSelector: 'grafana.app/get-history=true',
      fieldSelector: `metadata.name=${uid}`,
      limit: limit - result.items.length,
      continue: continueToken,
    });
    result.items.push(...nextPage.items);
    continueToken = nextPage.metadata.continue;
  }
  result.metadata.continue = continueToken;

  return result;
}
```

**Part 2: Fix `UnifiedDashboardAPI.listDashboardHistory` for mixed v1/v2**

With Part 1 in place, both v1 and v2 clients return fully paginated results. The `UnifiedDashboardAPI` should prefer v1 or v2 based on the `dashboardNewLayouts` feature flag, and only fall back to the other format when conversion failures are detected:

```typescript
async listDashboardHistory(uid: string, options?: ListDashboardHistoryOptions) {
  const limit = options?.limit ?? 10;
  const preferV2 = config.featureToggles.dashboardNewLayouts;

  const primary = preferV2 ? this.v2Client : this.v1Client;
  const secondary = preferV2 ? this.v1Client : this.v2Client;
  const primaryExclude = preferV2 ? ['v0', 'v1'] : ['v2'];
  const secondaryExclude = preferV2 ? ['v2'] : ['v0', 'v1'];

  const primaryResponse = await primary.listDashboardHistory(uid, { ...options, limit });
  const filteredPrimaryItems = primaryResponse.items.filter(
    (item) => !failedFromVersion(item, primaryExclude)
  );
  const hasConversionFailures = filteredPrimaryItems.length < primaryResponse.items.length;

  // Fall back to secondary if: conversion failures detected OR primary returned empty
  if (hasConversionFailures || primaryResponse.items.length === 0) {
    const secondaryResponse = await secondary.listDashboardHistory(uid, { ...options, limit });
    const filteredSecondaryItems = secondaryResponse.items.filter(
      (item) => !failedFromVersion(item, secondaryExclude)
    );

    const merged = [...filteredPrimaryItems, ...filteredSecondaryItems]
      .filter(isResource)
      .sort((a, b) => (b.metadata.generation ?? 0) - (a.metadata.generation ?? 0))
      .slice(0, limit);

    return { ...primaryResponse, items: merged };
  }

  return primaryResponse;
}
```

